   {:e #blake3 "7ea14ed1f521d5967bf7a98d1c91a602e234aa603503f345c6e64d1bae356ead" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "THE Y-COMBINATOR FOR LLMS. Braid IS the fixed-point combinator that gives stateless LLMs self-reference. The Y-combinator takes a function that can't recurse and gives it recursion via fixed point: f(Y(f)) = Y(f). An LLM is context->continuation with no memory, no self-model, no self-reference. Braid wraps it: seed->session->harvest->store->seed. When this converges, the seed contains exactly the information to produce the session that produces the harvest that produces the seed. Fixed point. Each capability braid adds is Y applied at a different level: Y(memory)=store+seed, Y(self-observation)=daemon, Y(learning)=calibration, Y(inquiry)=FEGH, Y(ontology)=Level 5. The attention mechanism (alpha=E[delta-F(S)]/cost) IS the transformer's attention at knowledge scale instead of token scale. The Hegelian dialectic (thesis/antithesis/synthesis = observation/comparison/reconciliation) IS the harvest/seed cycle IS Y iterating toward fixed point. The GPT was pretrained. Braid makes it post-trained: continuously learning through the same attention mechanism, at organizational knowledge scale.; Session entity: :task/t-fcfa6569; Session entity: :recon/trace-5220e5d141d1233d; Session entity: :recon/trace-0a60f17c280f2ec9; ADR-FOUNDATION-032: ONTOLOGICAL SURPRISE — detecting unknown unknowns via observation-schema gap analysis. The deepest gap in the introspective observer: FEGH detects missing BRIDGES between known clusters (known unknowns). But the capability census failure revealed missing CATEGORIES entirely (unknown unknowns). The store had zero :runtime/* datoms — not a sparse cluster, a complete void that spectral partition can't detect. FIX: The daemon watches the stream of agent observations for ontological novelty. Let S = attribute namespaces in schema, O = concept categories in observation text (topic clustering). The ontological gap = O minus S — concepts agents discuss that the store has no schema for. When gap detected, propose schema extension. This IS OBSERVER-6 (ontology discovery) from the three learning loops, connected to the daemon. The mechanism: (1) Topic clustering on :exploration/body text across sessions. (2) Map clusters to nearest schema namespace. (3) Clusters with no nearby namespace = ontological surprise. (4) Surface as: 'NEW CATEGORY DETECTED: agents discuss X but store has no :X/* attributes. Propose schema extension?' This is the system discovering its own blind spots by watching what users care about. It would have auto-generated SCHEMA-RUNTIME-1. Free energy interpretation: standard F measures KL divergence within existing dimensions. Ontological surprise measures the DIMENSIONALITY GAP — states in P(reality) with no representation in Q(model). TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, ADR-FOUNDATION-030, OBSERVER-6, C7.; Session entity: :task/t-bd434c69; Session entity: :recon/trace-74b334db1d7fdae7; ADR-FOUNDATION-033: LOAD-BEARING FAILURE DETECTION. Not all failures are equal. Some are bugs (low information, fix and move on). Others are load-bearing — they reveal structural truths that success would have hidden. The PERF-1 failure (misdiagnosed store loading) was load-bearing: it revealed reflexive divergence, the introspective observer, and the Y-combinator framing. None of these would have emerged from a successful implementation. MECHANISM: Three types of learning triggered by different failure signatures. Type 1 (calibration): prediction error is random, decreasing with data. Action: adjust weights. Type 2 (structure): prediction error is systematic, persisting across hypotheses. Action: reorganize model (FEGH bridges). Type 3 (ontology): failure doesn't fit ANY existing divergence type. Action: ontological inquiry (what category of knowledge is missing?). DETECTION: When per-type hypothesis accuracy is consistently low (mean error > 0.5 across 10+ hypotheses), escalate from Type 1 to Type 2. When a failure mode doesn't match Types 1-9, escalate to Type 3. TRIGGER: anomalous failure = a hypothesis outcome that doesn't fit any existing failure pattern. SURFACE: flag to user as potentially load-bearing. This IS the meta-cognitive skill that made Session 038 productive — noticing that the failure to diagnose correctly was itself informative. FORMALIZATION: aleatoric surprise (noise, ignore) vs epistemic surprise (signal, investigate). The distinction: epistemic surprise is SYSTEMATIC and doesn't decrease with more data. TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-030, ADR-FOUNDATION-032, INV-FOUNDATION-014.\nSession entity: :task/t-f0a1bf25" :op :assert}
